03:22.040 --> 03:24.930
- Come on, come on.
- Okay, all right.

03:25.080 --> 03:26.764
Will you hurry up?

03:38.040 --> 03:39.849
I'm home.

03:40.000 --> 03:41.570
Afternoon, Miss Edna.

03:41.720 --> 03:43.484
Penny, your mother called.

03:43.640 --> 03:46.849
Tracy Turnblad, can't you
say hello to Mrs. Malinski?

03:47.000 --> 03:48.445
Mm, mm, mm.

03:48.600 --> 03:52.844
Every day she's got to watch that
<i>Corny Collins Show.</i>

03:53.040 --> 03:54.929
Delinquents, if you ask me.

03:55.080 --> 03:58.368
It ain't right to be dancing
on TV to that colored music.

03:58.520 --> 04:01.330
- She's just a teenager.
- Hmph.

04:02.040 --> 04:04.725
- Goodbye, Mrs. Malinski.
- Goodbye, Edna.

04:09.840 --> 04:13.367
<i>Mashed Potato
Feel it in your feet now</i>

04:13.560 --> 04:16.608
<i>Mashed Potato
Come on get the beat now</i>

04:16.760 --> 04:22.005
<i>Baby, come on honey,
come on baby</i>

04:23.720 --> 04:25.802
Could you turn that racket down?

04:25.960 --> 04:29.885
I'm trying to iron in here.

04:32.080 --> 04:35.482
<i>They found this dance
was outta sight</i>

04:35.640 --> 04:39.725
<i>Doin' the lion sleeps tonight</i>

04:39.920 --> 04:45.404
<i>Mashed Potato</i>

04:47.520 --> 04:48.567
Woo, yeah

04:48.760 --> 04:51.445
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,
Corny Collins.</i>

04:51.680 --> 04:54.604
Good afternoon, Baltimore, and welcome
to <i>The Corny Collins Show.</i>

04:57.200 --> 04:58.964
That was Dee Dee Sharp
and today's...

04:59.120 --> 05:01.000
Thwip. ...Bull's-eye hit,
"Mashed Potato Time."

05:02.360 --> 05:04.522
We've got our first
telegram of the day.

05:04.720 --> 05:07.200
Thank you very much, Tammy.

05:07.360 --> 05:10.284
"Please have Lou Ann Levorowski
and I.Q. Jones lead a dance."

05:10.440 --> 05:12.727
Signed, "your number one fan
in West Baltimore."

05:12.880 --> 05:14.644
Here they come.
Come up here, kids.

05:14.800 --> 05:16.484
- Hi, Corny.
- Hi, West Baltimore.

05:16.640 --> 05:19.962
You're a groovy chick. How long have
you been a regular on the show?

05:20.120 --> 05:21.828
I've been on the
Council for five months.

05:21.854 --> 05:22.625
And you, I.Q.?

05:22.800 --> 05:23.881
Two out-of-sight years.

05:25.240 --> 05:26.321
Heh, not bad.

05:26.480 --> 05:28.562
God, he's gorgeous, Penny.

05:28.760 --> 05:29.807
- Look at her hair.
- Aah!

05:29.960 --> 05:31.480
Gosh, I wish mine was that high.

05:31.600 --> 05:33.887
<i>And what's your favorite
record from the survey?</i>

05:34.040 --> 05:35.371
<i>"Gravy."</i>

05:35.560 --> 05:38.131
<i>All right, here's I. Q. Jones
and Lou Ann Levorowski...</i>

05:38.280 --> 05:41.250
<i>leading our next dance,
Give Me Gravy on my Mashed Potatoes.</i>

05:44.160 --> 05:46.970
<i>I need gravy
Give me, give me</i>

05:47.120 --> 05:49.441
<i>Give me, give me gravy tonight</i>

05:49.600 --> 05:53.161
<i>I knew you danced
The mashed potato fine</i>

05:53.320 --> 05:56.369
<i>But that don't show me
That you're really mine</i>

05:57.120 --> 06:00.090
<i>What's with dancin'
Without romancin'?</i>

06:00.240 --> 06:03.847
<i>So put that somethin'
extra on the line</i>

06:04.000 --> 06:06.924
<i>Give me gravy
On my mashed potatoes</i>

06:07.080 --> 06:10.846
<i>Give me gravy
Come on and treat me right</i>

06:11.000 --> 06:14.721
<i>Give me gravy
You're the greatest</i>

06:14.880 --> 06:19.488
<i>So give me, give me
Give me, give me gravy tonight</i>

06:23.240 --> 06:25.720
Link, tell the home viewers
where we'll be tonight.

06:25.880 --> 06:28.121
Well, Corny, we'll be
at the Parkville VFW.

06:28.320 --> 06:30.482
For the Corny Collins Record Hop.

06:30.640 --> 06:33.211
Stuck-up little spastic.

06:33.360 --> 06:34.805
She's such a queer.

06:34.960 --> 06:37.725
<i>Parkville VFW, 8:00.
What do you want to hear, Amber?</i>

06:37.880 --> 06:40.281
"Shake a Tail Feather"
by The Five Du-Tones.

06:40.440 --> 06:42.283
Here they are, The Five Du-Tones.

06:49.800 --> 06:53.168
<i>I heard about the fella
You've been dancin' with</i>

06:53.320 --> 06:56.085
<i>All over the neighborhood</i>

06:56.240 --> 06:59.323
<i>So why didn't you ask me, baby?</i>

06:59.520 --> 07:02.091
<i>Or didn't you think I could?</i>

07:02.240 --> 07:05.403
<i>I know that the Bossa Nova's
Outta sight</i>

07:05.560 --> 07:08.086
<i>I've seen him do
the Bird all night</i>

07:08.280 --> 07:11.329
<i>But, if that was you and me
Out there, baby</i>

07:11.480 --> 07:14.689
<i>I would have shown you
How to do it right</i>

07:14.840 --> 07:15.588
<i>Do it right</i>

07:21.640 --> 07:29.640
<i>Bend over
Let me see you shake a tail feather</i>

07:33.600 --> 07:39.004
<i>Twistin'! Shake-it, shake-it, shake-it
Shake-it, baby</i>

07:39.160 --> 07:41.367
You should be on
that council, not her.

07:41.560 --> 07:44.962
I know I should, Penny.
Hey, I'm going to that hop tonight.

07:45.120 --> 07:48.602
Oh, let me come. We'll lie and say
we're going to the library to study.

07:48.760 --> 07:50.285
- It's a deal, heh.
- Heh.

07:50.440 --> 07:52.966
- We'll meet 8:00, up on the avenue.
- Heh.

07:53.120 --> 07:56.966
Okay, young ladies. I've had just
about enough of this screeching music.

07:57.160 --> 07:59.561
Mother, we're watching
<i>The Corny Collins Show.</i>

08:00.520 --> 08:02.568
Penny,
your mother called all frantic.

08:02.720 --> 08:04.131
She said you are punished.

08:04.280 --> 08:05.884
I'm always punished.

08:06.040 --> 08:08.566
And Tracy, I have told
you about that hair...

08:08.720 --> 08:11.530
all ratted up like
a teenage Jezebel.

08:11.760 --> 08:13.603
Oh, Mother,
you're so '50s.

08:13.840 --> 08:17.003
Tracy's flamboyant flip
is all the rage, Miss Edna.

08:17.160 --> 08:20.209
Jackie Kennedy, our first lady,
even rats her hair.

08:20.360 --> 08:23.364
But Tracy ain't no
first lady, are you, Tracy?

08:23.560 --> 08:27.042
No, sirree, she's a hairhopper.
That's what she is.

08:27.200 --> 08:30.647
Now, I've got nothing but
hampers of ironing to do...

08:30.800 --> 08:33.041
and my diet pill is wearing off.

08:33.520 --> 08:36.602
Tracy, I want you to go
to your room and study.

08:36.760 --> 08:38.568
And Penny,
don't you be listening...

08:38.720 --> 08:41.121
to every bit of nonsense
my daughter tells you.

08:41.880 --> 08:44.770
If I didn't know better,
I'd swear she was mental.

08:46.160 --> 08:50.165
Now what? More soiled laundry
for Mommy, I suppose.

08:50.320 --> 08:52.243
Come in.

08:52.400 --> 08:54.482
Edna, have you seen Penny?

08:54.640 --> 08:56.961
Good Lord, Prudy,
she's right over there.

08:58.240 --> 08:59.321
Hi, Mom.

08:59.480 --> 09:02.245
Penny Pingleton,
you know you were punished.

09:02.400 --> 09:06.041
From now on, you're wearing a giant P
on your blouse every day to school...

09:06.200 --> 09:10.444
so that the whole world knows that
Penny Pingleton is permanently...

09:10.600 --> 09:12.409
positively punished.

09:13.840 --> 09:14.887
Eight o'clock.

09:15.040 --> 09:17.088
- Bye, Miss Edna.
- Bye, honey.

10:11.640 --> 10:13.608
I said no.

10:31.200 --> 10:34.329
- Oh, stop. Stop, unh.
- What is it? What is it?

10:34.480 --> 10:36.289
Unh, oh, my God.

10:38.120 --> 10:40.122
- Amber, what's the matter?
- No, get off of me.

10:40.320 --> 10:43.130
- Don't look at me.
- Whoa, what's the matter? Amber.

10:48.040 --> 10:49.405
What's the matter?

10:49.560 --> 10:52.040
I happen to have a blemish.

10:54.840 --> 10:57.047
You had three good
close-ups today, period.

10:57.200 --> 11:00.010
Why can't you dance up front
where the voters can see you?

11:00.160 --> 11:01.924
Leave me alone, Mother.
I have a pimple.

11:02.080 --> 11:05.402
Heh, you had to choose a colored
record as your favorite song?

11:05.600 --> 11:07.409
That's nice for the neighbors.

11:07.600 --> 11:09.921
You got something against
Connie Francis?

11:10.080 --> 11:11.366
Shelley Fabares?

11:11.560 --> 11:13.449
- I love Shelley Fabares.
- Oh.

11:13.600 --> 11:15.489
Amber, Amber.

11:15.640 --> 11:17.324
Are you listening to me?

11:18.680 --> 11:21.411
We have to have a little talk.

11:21.560 --> 11:24.564
You know, if your father is
forced to integrate Tilted Acres...

11:24.720 --> 11:26.165
we're out of business.

11:26.320 --> 11:28.971
So at least act
white on television.

11:29.160 --> 11:30.286
Leave me alone, Mother.

11:30.440 --> 11:32.568
"Shake a Tail Feather"
is a wild song.

11:32.720 --> 11:34.927
It's got a good beat
and you can dance to it.

11:35.080 --> 11:36.286
Oh, God, of all nights.

11:36.440 --> 11:39.808
A Corny Collins record hop,
and I've got craters.

11:39.960 --> 11:42.327
Unh, just pop it. Pop it.

11:42.480 --> 11:44.323
Just relax. Relax.

11:44.480 --> 11:47.131
Don't be ridiculous.
Take it easy.

11:47.280 --> 11:50.250
Tension is the worst thing
for a complexion.

11:50.400 --> 11:52.846
Come on. Lie down. Lie down.

11:53.000 --> 11:54.604
No moping.

11:56.440 --> 11:58.602
Mother is here.

11:59.440 --> 12:02.046
You have beautiful skin, Amber.

12:05.680 --> 12:08.763
There. It's gone.

12:08.920 --> 12:12.322
<i>Now it's time for you-know-what</i>

12:12.480 --> 12:14.767
Mother, I know all the dances.

12:14.960 --> 12:18.169
Come on. Get up. Get up.

12:18.320 --> 12:20.004
- Practice makes perfect.
- Ugh.

12:20.160 --> 12:21.924
I ought to know.

12:22.080 --> 12:25.050
Don't forget, I was
Miss Soft Crab in 1945.

12:25.240 --> 12:29.040
And that title wasn't handed to me
on a silver platter. I worked for it.

12:29.200 --> 12:34.650
Now come on. A one, two,
a one, two, three, pony.

12:36.040 --> 12:38.441
Mash potatoes.

12:39.120 --> 12:40.929
Faster.

12:44.640 --> 12:46.244
Amber, I'd like to talk to you.

12:46.600 --> 12:47.806
Yes, Daddy?

12:48.000 --> 12:49.764
Don't stop. Cha-cha.

12:49.920 --> 12:52.287
- I'm tired.
- One, two, cha-cha-cha.

12:52.440 --> 12:54.010
One, two, cha-cha-cha.

12:54.160 --> 13:00.566
I had some new campaign fliers made up
today, all for Daddy's little girl.

13:00.720 --> 13:03.929
Now, I want you to hand those out
at the hop tonight to everyone.

13:04.080 --> 13:05.923
Each and every one of those.

13:06.080 --> 13:08.321
- Twist.
- Oh, Daddy, ugh.

13:08.480 --> 13:11.131
No lip from you, Miss ingrate.

13:11.280 --> 13:13.647
This campaign is costing us
an arm and a leg.

13:13.800 --> 13:16.929
New gowns,
hairdresser three times a week.

13:17.080 --> 13:21.130
Your hairspray bill alone is enough to eat
up all the profits from the Tilt-A-Whirl.

13:21.320 --> 13:24.847
Do as Daddy says or we'll send you
to Catholic school where you belong.

13:25.000 --> 13:27.401
- Right, Franklin?
- That's right. Catholic school.

13:28.520 --> 13:31.967
Pass the macaroni
and cheese, please.

13:32.160 --> 13:35.767
Did you take that appetite suppressant
I gave you on Dr. McKenzie's orders?

13:35.960 --> 13:38.440
Mother, I'm a growing teenager.
I need food.

13:39.040 --> 13:40.690
Let her eat, Edna.

13:40.880 --> 13:43.565
Tracy, did you do your chores
around the house today?

13:45.360 --> 13:48.204
Not Miss Tracy,
Cyd Charisse herself.

13:48.360 --> 13:52.490
She's too busy ratting her hair
and doing the Ubangi stomp.

13:52.720 --> 13:56.725
Tracy, we all have
responsibilities in life.

13:56.880 --> 13:59.884
You may think owning the Hardy
Har joke shop is all drudgery...

14:00.040 --> 14:03.362
unwrapping dribble glasses,
checking doggie doo inventory...

14:03.520 --> 14:04.646
but I love it.

14:06.720 --> 14:09.326
You'll see. Work can be fun.

14:09.480 --> 14:13.166
Can I please be excused to go
to the library to study?

14:17.000 --> 14:19.287
<i>Let's have a ball
at the hall tonight</i>

14:19.440 --> 14:22.649
<i>Boot it girl till
the early bright</i>

14:22.840 --> 14:27.846
<i>Make a scene with the record machine
At the dancin' party tonight</i>

14:28.000 --> 14:29.968
<i>Come on let's try
mashed potatoes too</i>

14:30.120 --> 14:31.451
What's the problem, officer?

14:31.640 --> 14:33.802
- This is a white establishment.
- Oh, come on.

14:33.960 --> 14:36.281
Hey, listen,
we just came to dance.

14:38.000 --> 14:41.209
- That's not fair.
- Open your purse, please.

14:42.520 --> 14:45.000
<i>And everything's all right</i>

14:46.320 --> 14:49.449
Go. Go.

14:51.080 --> 14:53.924
<i>Mess around, Bristol Stompin' too</i>

14:54.120 --> 14:56.407
<i>Pony now like it's all brand new</i>

14:56.560 --> 14:58.847
<i>Any dance that you wanna do</i>

15:04.640 --> 15:08.486
Boys and girls, stay on the dance floor.
Here comes the hottest tune of the day.

15:08.640 --> 15:11.166
And it started right
here in Baltimore.

15:15.880 --> 15:18.326
And where did you
see it first, kids?

15:18.560 --> 15:21.689
<i>The Corny Collins Show.</i>

15:21.880 --> 15:26.841
A big strong line, ladies and
gentlemen. It's "Madison Time."

15:27.880 --> 15:29.086
I can do that dance.

15:34.160 --> 15:36.845
<i>It's Madison time, hit it</i>

15:40.000 --> 15:43.209
<i>You're lookin' good
A big strong line</i>

15:45.320 --> 15:48.403
<i>When I say hit it I want you
to go two up and two back</i>

15:48.560 --> 15:52.087
<i>With a big strong turn
and back to the Madison</i>

15:53.080 --> 15:54.127
<i>Hit it</i>

15:54.280 --> 15:57.045
No, you dance better than
all of them. Go ahead. Go.

15:58.240 --> 15:59.446
<i>You're lookin' good</i>

16:02.200 --> 16:05.568
<i>Now when I say hit it I want
you to go two up and two back</i>

16:05.720 --> 16:09.441
<i>Double cross
Come out of it with the rifleman</i>

16:10.440 --> 16:12.169
<i>Hit it</i>

16:22.080 --> 16:23.605
Crazy

16:23.760 --> 16:26.240
<i>Now when I say hit it
I want the big strong "M"</i>

16:26.400 --> 16:28.971
<i>Erase it,
and back to the Madison</i>

16:30.400 --> 16:32.050
<i>Hit it</i>

16:35.960 --> 16:37.724
<i>Walk on, you're lookin' good</i>

16:46.480 --> 16:50.326
<i>Now then when I say hit it
It'll be "T" time</i>

16:53.040 --> 16:54.485
<i>Hit it</i>

17:01.560 --> 17:02.607
<i>Big strong line</i>

17:03.800 --> 17:06.723
<i>Now when I say hit it
I want the big strong basketball</i>

17:06.920 --> 17:09.491
<i>With the Wilt Chamberlain hook</i>

17:12.480 --> 17:14.005
<i>Hit it</i>

17:15.280 --> 17:17.203
<i>Two points</i>

17:19.760 --> 17:21.967
<i>Now this time when I say hit it</i>

17:22.119 --> 17:25.761
<i>I want the big strong Jackie Gleason
And back to the Madison</i>

17:27.760 --> 17:29.125
<i>Hit it</i>

17:31.400 --> 17:33.050
<i>And away we go</i>

17:34.760 --> 17:35.841
Crazy

17:36.000 --> 17:39.561
<i>When I say hit it, go two up
and two back double cross and freeze</i>

17:39.720 --> 17:41.165
<i>Hit it</i>

17:47.840 --> 17:50.684
<i>And hold it right there</i>

17:57.360 --> 18:00.364
All right. Hold on to your hats,
all you continental rockers...

18:00.520 --> 18:04.570
because it's dance contest time,
and we've got the wildest judge in town.

18:04.720 --> 18:08.042
You listen to her every night on WEDD
and she hosts Negro Day...

18:08.200 --> 18:11.204
on <i>The Corny Collins Show.</i>
The last Thursday of every month.

18:11.400 --> 18:14.529
A warm welcome for the queen
of Baltimore soul...

18:14.680 --> 18:17.968
Miss Motormouth Maybelle herself,
ladies and gentlemen.

18:18.120 --> 18:21.044
Let's hear it, Baltimore.
Motormouth Maybelle.

18:21.240 --> 18:25.529
All right, here she comes,
looking very fine.

18:25.720 --> 18:31.409
Ooh, wee, tiddley papa,
I am a whopper.

18:33.600 --> 18:40.722
Motormouth Maybelle is my name
and, sweetheart, dancing is my game.

18:42.240 --> 18:44.971
Motormouth, Motormouth,
Motormouth.

18:45.120 --> 18:46.281
All right.

18:46.440 --> 18:50.525
Chubby Checker and "Pony Time."

18:54.280 --> 19:00.287
<i>Hey now let's party
In the union hall</i>

19:00.440 --> 19:05.128
<i>It's pony time
When you hear this call</i>

19:06.560 --> 19:10.451
<i>So get with it
Don't quit it</i>

19:10.600 --> 19:12.489
<i>Get up</i>

19:12.640 --> 19:15.723
Okay, fatso, let's see
what you're made of.

19:15.920 --> 19:18.969
<i>With a big boss line</i>

19:19.120 --> 19:22.010
<i>Well anyway you do it</i>

19:22.160 --> 19:23.924
<i>You're gonna look real fine</i>

19:25.160 --> 19:29.051
<i>So get with it
Don't quit it</i>

19:29.200 --> 19:30.964
<i>Get up</i>

19:32.200 --> 19:35.647
<i>Now you turn to the left
When I say gee</i>

19:35.800 --> 19:38.371
<i>You turn to the right
When I say haw</i>

19:38.520 --> 19:41.364
<i>Now gee
Yeah, yeah, little baby</i>

19:41.520 --> 19:45.684
<i>Now haw
Yeah, oh, baby</i>

19:45.840 --> 19:48.764
<i>Oh, baby, pony baby</i>

19:48.920 --> 19:54.131
<i>Do it, baby
Oh, baby, oh, baby</i>

19:54.280 --> 19:56.123
<i>Boogety, boogety, boogety, boogety</i>

19:56.280 --> 20:02.162
<i>Gonna see little Suzie
Who lives next door</i>

20:02.320 --> 20:05.210
<i>She's doin' the pony</i>

20:05.360 --> 20:08.250
<i>She's takin' the floor</i>

20:09.080 --> 20:11.526
<i>So get with it
Don't quit it</i>

20:18.400 --> 20:20.323
All right.

20:20.480 --> 20:23.529
All right, Motormouth,
just three couples left.

20:23.720 --> 20:25.404
Tammy,
bring on the applause meter.

20:26.800 --> 20:29.690
Is it going to be
couple number one?

20:34.520 --> 20:36.522
Or is it couple number two?

20:39.360 --> 20:42.603
Or shall it be couple
number three?

20:52.320 --> 20:54.163
All right.

20:54.320 --> 20:56.607
I think we have a winner.

20:56.760 --> 20:58.649
And that winner is...

20:58.800 --> 21:02.964
I love them tender,
Tracy and Fender.

21:03.120 --> 21:04.485
All right.

21:05.360 --> 21:07.966
Tracy Turnblad and Fender.

21:12.880 --> 21:15.406
Tracy Turnblad, you are the
queen of the hop tonight.

21:15.560 --> 21:19.406
We hold auditions for the Council
tomorrow. Come down, strut your stuff.

21:19.560 --> 21:21.562
Oh, Corny, do you really think
I'm good enough?

21:21.720 --> 21:22.801
What do you think, Kids?

21:22.960 --> 21:24.803
Yeah!

21:26.880 --> 21:30.043
I hear you. Thanks for coming down,
Tracy. We'll see you tomorrow.

21:30.200 --> 21:33.522
Now, Motormouth, I think it's time
we slowed things down a little...

21:33.680 --> 21:34.966
with Mr. Gene Pitney.

21:35.120 --> 21:39.045
You can't hide your face
in this godforsaken place.

21:39.200 --> 21:43.569
Here in your own city,
there's a town without pity, heh.

21:43.720 --> 21:45.484
Gene Pitney,
ladies and gentlemen.

21:58.160 --> 22:04.281
