24:01.000 --> 24:02.764
Thank you, girls.

24:02.960 --> 24:07.409
And now it's time to move on to a
little something we call the spotlight.

24:11.960 --> 24:15.965
Okay. First girl, Miss Pingleton?

24:17.800 --> 24:19.723
Uh, I'm just a little nervous.

24:19.920 --> 24:21.968
This is show business, young lady.

24:22.120 --> 24:24.122
If you think you're
nervous now, ha.

24:24.280 --> 24:26.328
Wait till you're on the air.

24:26.520 --> 24:28.966
Okay, first question?

24:30.560 --> 24:34.087
Are you now, or have
you ever gone steady?

24:34.320 --> 24:37.529
Well, I'm not going with anybody now,
but I'd love to date a Council Member.

24:37.680 --> 24:39.489
- Pfft. She wishes.
- Yeah, right.

24:40.960 --> 24:42.041
Come on.

24:42.200 --> 24:44.282
Exactly how many
sweaters do you have?

24:44.480 --> 24:46.209
Gee, I never counted.

24:46.360 --> 24:48.010
I guess about five.

24:48.360 --> 24:49.646
Five?

24:52.360 --> 24:53.521
Next.

24:54.200 --> 24:58.171
Nadine Carver,
Eastern High School.

24:58.320 --> 25:01.369
Are you aware Negro Day is the
last Thursday of every month?

25:01.560 --> 25:04.211
Yes, I've been on it a few times.

25:04.480 --> 25:08.280
I feel the show should be
integrated every day.

25:10.040 --> 25:12.008
Can you relate
to Lesley Gore's music?

25:13.480 --> 25:16.211
Look, she ain't no James Brown...

25:16.360 --> 25:20.445
but I can dance to
Lawrence Welk if I have to.

25:20.600 --> 25:22.568
Lawrence Welk?

25:22.720 --> 25:24.131
Thank you, Nadine.

25:24.720 --> 25:26.324
Tracy Turnblad.

25:33.280 --> 25:36.443
Would you do a pimple cream
commercial on camera...

25:36.680 --> 25:38.409
if Corny asked you to?

25:38.560 --> 25:39.891
I'd be proud to.

25:40.280 --> 25:44.171
Luckily, I've never been cursed
with acne like others.

25:44.800 --> 25:47.121
But I realize the devastating
effect of skin blemishes...

25:47.280 --> 25:48.964
on the social life of teenagers.

25:50.360 --> 25:55.924
Would you ever, heh, swim in
an integrated swimming pool, heh?

25:56.080 --> 25:57.127
Oh, my God.

25:58.520 --> 25:59.806
- I certainly would, Iggy.
- Heh.

25:59.960 --> 26:01.325
I'm a modern kind of girl.

26:01.480 --> 26:03.130
I'm all for integration.

26:03.280 --> 26:05.567
Ugh, aren't you a little fat
for the show?

26:05.720 --> 26:07.006
That's enough, Amber.

26:07.520 --> 26:11.605
I would imagine that many home viewers
are also pleasantly plump or chunky.

26:11.760 --> 26:14.525
Oh, come on. The show's
not filmed in CinemaScope, heh.

26:14.680 --> 26:15.841
You're out of line, Amber.

26:16.000 --> 26:18.571
- Ow.
- Corny, Tammy, can't you see?

26:18.760 --> 26:21.491
- This girl's a trash can.
- That's five demerit points.

26:21.680 --> 26:24.763
You're suspended from the show today.
Pack your things. Go home.

26:24.920 --> 26:26.251
Oh, my God.

26:26.400 --> 26:30.883
- I was supposed to lead ladies' choice.
- I'm sure we can find a replacement.

26:32.520 --> 26:35.126
- Yes, Corny.
- Please, wait outside.

26:35.320 --> 26:39.086
The Council will now meet in secret,
debate your personality flaws...

26:39.280 --> 26:42.045
and come to a final decision.

26:45.320 --> 26:47.004
Miss Edna!

26:47.160 --> 26:49.447
Miss Edna!

26:49.600 --> 26:51.568
Penny Pingleton,
you'll wake the dead.

26:51.720 --> 26:53.006
Tracy's not home yet.

26:53.160 --> 26:55.925
Plus your mother called
and she's on the warpath.

26:56.080 --> 26:57.684
I know, Miss Edna.
Can I come in?

26:57.880 --> 26:59.803
Oh, there's something
you have gotta see.

26:59.960 --> 27:01.803
Well, yeah, come on up...

27:01.960 --> 27:05.328
but I've got ironing
and Wilbur's working.

27:05.480 --> 27:07.926
Mr. Turnblad!

27:13.720 --> 27:16.451
It's not war with Cuba, is it?

27:16.640 --> 27:19.041
- Or more Negro problems?
- No, you'll see.

27:19.240 --> 27:22.323
Did poor Debbie Reynolds
have a nervous breakdown?

27:22.480 --> 27:23.686
This better be good.

27:23.840 --> 27:27.162
Broad daylight and I'm sitting
in front of a TV.

27:27.320 --> 27:29.527
I've seen <i>The Corny Collins Show.</i>,
thank you.

27:29.680 --> 27:34.049
- Just watch.
- I just lost a $2.69 Silly Putty sale.

27:34.200 --> 27:37.283
- This better be worth it.
- Wait, you'll see. Just watch.

27:37.480 --> 27:38.845
<i>- What's your name?
- I'm Ruby.</i>

27:39.000 --> 27:40.445
<i>- And you?
- Dee Dee.</i>

27:40.600 --> 27:42.409
<i>- What about you?
- I'm Lucille.</i>

27:42.560 --> 27:44.324
<i>Where will you
be appearing tonight?</i>

27:44.480 --> 27:45.845
<i>We'll be at the Royal Theater.</i>

27:46.000 --> 27:49.322
<i>- At Motormouth Maybelle
- All soul review.</i>

27:49.560 --> 27:51.164
<i>All right, ladies and gentlemen...</i>

27:51.320 --> 27:53.527
<i>a big hand for Baltimore's
own Trinklettes.</i>

27:53.680 --> 27:55.444
I closed up shop for this?

27:55.600 --> 27:56.965
Just wait.

27:57.120 --> 27:58.645
<i>Let's keep the music playing...</i>

27:58.800 --> 28:00.882
<i>and the hits a-turning
with Mr. Gene Chandler...</i>

28:01.040 --> 28:04.010
<i>because the Duke of Earl
loves to cha-cha.</i>

28:06.280 --> 28:07.691
There, there. Look.

28:07.840 --> 28:09.205
It's Tracy.

28:09.360 --> 28:12.842
Oh, my God.
She's all peroxided up.

28:13.720 --> 28:16.485
I'll be damned. Tracy's on TV.

28:16.640 --> 28:18.130
With a triple process, yet.

28:18.280 --> 28:21.443
But Tracy was accepted
on the Corny Collins Council.

28:21.600 --> 28:25.400
Mr. and Mrs. Turnblad,
your daughter's a star.

28:27.120 --> 28:30.602
<i>And you, you are my girl</i>

28:30.760 --> 28:34.810
<i>And no one can hurt you, oh, no</i>

28:34.960 --> 28:37.247
See? She's already
getting close-ups.

28:37.440 --> 28:39.169
Does she get paid for this?

28:39.720 --> 28:43.042
- Big as a house.
- I think she looks pretty, Edna, heh.

28:50.840 --> 28:52.808
Hello.

28:53.000 --> 28:56.447
Uh, yes, I'm watching her now.

28:57.040 --> 28:59.281
You are? Well, thank you, heh.

28:59.440 --> 29:02.284
Yes. Good bye.

29:03.320 --> 29:05.482
That was Hilda
from up Conklin Street.

29:05.680 --> 29:07.250
She's going to send a telegram.

29:09.280 --> 29:12.284
Oh, God, there she is.

29:21.520 --> 29:24.569
<i>Nothing can stop me, now</i>

29:24.720 --> 29:29.169
<i>'Cause I'm the Duke of Earl</i>

29:29.320 --> 29:32.688
<i>So, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah</i>

29:39.640 --> 29:42.041
It's time to introduce someone
very special.

29:42.200 --> 29:45.204
A new Council Member making
her first appearance on the show...

29:45.360 --> 29:47.886
and we already have telegrams.
Introduce yourself.

29:48.040 --> 29:52.682
Hi, Corny. I'm Tracy Turnblad
and I go to Mervel High.

29:56.200 --> 29:58.043
Well, someone out there likes you.

29:58.200 --> 30:01.090
"Please, have the new girl
lead a ladies' choice."

30:01.280 --> 30:03.567
I was supposed to lead
the ladies' choice.

30:03.880 --> 30:06.451
<i>- Tell me, Tracy, are you going steady?
- No, I'm not.</i>

30:06.600 --> 30:08.807
<i>But there is somebody
I've got a crush on.</i>

30:08.960 --> 30:12.931
Who, I'd like to know?
She's just a child.

30:13.480 --> 30:15.448
<i>Well, let's see who
the lucky guy is.</i>

30:15.600 --> 30:18.126
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,
a ladies' choice.</i>

30:18.520 --> 30:20.363
Hi, Tracy. It's me, Penny.

30:20.520 --> 30:22.329
She can't hear you.

30:26.160 --> 30:29.289
She better hadn't dare.

30:32.160 --> 30:36.085
<i>If you should lose me</i>

30:37.320 --> 30:39.641
<i>Oh, yeah</i>

30:39.800 --> 30:42.167
<i>You'll lose a good thing</i>

30:46.320 --> 30:50.245
<i>If you should lose me</i>

30:51.640 --> 30:53.529
<i>Oh, yeah</i>

30:53.680 --> 30:58.004
<i>You'll lose a good thing</i>

31:02.440 --> 31:05.410
<i>You know I love you</i>

31:05.560 --> 31:09.451
<i>Do anything for you</i>

31:09.600 --> 31:15.164
Ugh, oh, God. He's violated the
oath of the friendship ring.

31:20.320 --> 31:21.481
Oh, don't cry, honey.

31:22.000 --> 31:25.402
<i>You'll lose a good thing</i>

31:30.560 --> 31:33.564
<i>I'm givin' you one more chance</i>

31:33.720 --> 31:36.291
<i>For you to do right</i>

31:37.680 --> 31:42.686
<i>If you'll only straighten up
We'll have a good life</i>

31:42.840 --> 31:44.649
That fat girl's no competition.

31:44.800 --> 31:47.246
White trash, plain and simple.

31:47.400 --> 31:50.847
For all we know,
that girl could be high yellow.

31:51.000 --> 31:55.961
Oh, Mommy, Daddy, I'll still be
the queen of the auto show, won't I?

31:56.120 --> 31:58.441
Oh, honey.

32:05.160 --> 32:08.448
Tracy!

32:08.600 --> 32:10.602
Tracy.

32:17.800 --> 32:20.246
No, she's not here.

32:20.400 --> 32:22.687
Well, I'm sure she loves you too.

32:23.040 --> 32:25.964
Yes, thank you. Goodbye.

32:26.120 --> 32:27.531
This is amazing.

32:28.000 --> 32:29.809
She's so popular already.

32:30.240 --> 32:32.641
She could be one of
The June Taylor Dancers.

32:39.280 --> 32:40.930
Hello.

32:41.080 --> 32:45.961
Well, yes,
I am Tracy Turnblad's agent.

32:46.120 --> 32:48.726
Give me a pencil. Quick, quick.

32:51.800 --> 32:53.882
How may I help you?

32:54.040 --> 32:55.326
Mm-hm, mm-hm.

32:56.720 --> 32:57.767
Here's Tracy.

32:59.720 --> 33:01.449
Oh, Tracy, you were wonderful.

33:01.600 --> 33:04.365
- Honey, we're real proud of you.
- We'll be there.

33:04.520 --> 33:05.681
Oh, sweetie, listen.

33:05.840 --> 33:08.730
Tomorrow, get up just a bit
closer so we can see you better.

33:08.920 --> 33:12.083
And maybe even give the Hardy
Har a little p-p-p plug, heh.

33:12.240 --> 33:14.481
Oh, Mom, Dad.

33:14.640 --> 33:17.291
Oh, Penny, my best friend.

33:17.440 --> 33:19.124
I'm so happy.

33:19.280 --> 33:25.367
Finally all of Baltimore knows,
I'm big, blond and beautiful.

33:25.560 --> 33:27.289
You're a teen leader now.

33:27.480 --> 33:30.131
And the show biz offers
are pouring in.

33:30.280 --> 33:33.329
Tonight we have an audition.
Honey, this is only the beginning.

33:33.480 --> 33:35.960
Stick with me and we'll
claw our way to the top.

33:36.120 --> 33:37.406
Oh, God.

33:37.560 --> 33:42.202
Fame, fortune, glamour.

33:42.360 --> 33:44.681
And to top it off...

33:46.200 --> 33:48.328
- ...I'm in love.
- Oh.

33:50.440 --> 33:53.887
Wow, Tracy, you're really tough.

34:09.199 --> 34:12.806
Oh, ooh, Tracy, what do
you think about this one?

34:12.960 --> 34:14.007
- I like it.
- Oh.

34:14.159 --> 34:16.367
Wilbur would kill us
if we spent that much.

34:16.520 --> 34:19.045
You look gorgeous, Bertha.
Simply exquisite.

34:19.239 --> 34:22.641
- Oh, I don't know, Pinky.
- Have an éclair.

34:22.800 --> 34:23.960
Oh.

34:24.159 --> 34:26.891
Eat up, girls. Eat up.
Big is beautiful.

34:27.080 --> 34:29.047
Tracy Turnblad.

34:29.199 --> 34:32.409
Welcome to the Hefty Hideaway house
of fashion for the ample woman.

34:32.560 --> 34:35.210
- Hi, I'm Mr. Pinky.
- Hi.

34:35.360 --> 34:39.284
Mr. Pinky, I'm Tracy's business
manager, Edna Turnblad.

34:39.440 --> 34:41.726
Well, it's a pleasure
to meet the both of you.

34:41.880 --> 34:45.009
Here, we cater to big-boned gals
like yourself who are stylish...

34:45.159 --> 34:48.721
and at the same time frustrated
by the lack of sizes in stores today.

34:48.880 --> 34:51.770
I saw you on TV.
I want you to be my model.

34:51.920 --> 34:54.366
Would, uh...?
Would she be paid for this?

34:54.560 --> 34:55.971
One free outfit a month.

34:56.199 --> 34:59.044
You start tomorrow. I hope
there's no diets in the works...

34:59.240 --> 35:02.961
because I want to design your Miss
Auto Show coronation gown myself.

35:03.680 --> 35:07.048
Could, uh, could you throw a pair of
complimentary pettipants in the deal?

35:07.200 --> 35:10.124
You drive a hard bargain,
Miss Edna, and rightfully so.

35:10.280 --> 35:13.523
Pettipants, pettigirdle,
you just let Tracy take her pick.

35:14.040 --> 35:16.247
How about a fabulous
frock just for me?

35:16.440 --> 35:18.351
Tracy has to work one
extra day for free.

35:18.377 --> 35:19.150
It's a deal.

35:19.280 --> 35:21.123
- Thank you, Mr. Pinky.
- Ha-ha-ha.

35:21.280 --> 35:24.682
I'm going to make you a star.

35:30.160 --> 35:31.446
I hope your father likes this.

35:31.600 --> 35:34.080
He'll love it. You look beautiful.
It's the new you.

35:35.480 --> 35:37.801
Oh, mom, come on. Come on.

35:37.960 --> 35:39.246
- Go in the beauty shop?
- Yes.

35:39.400 --> 35:41.243
- You haven't done that in years.
- No, ha, ha.

35:41.400 --> 35:43.846
- Come on. You deserve it.
- No, Wilbur will kill me.

35:44.000 --> 35:45.889
- Come on.
- Oh, okay.

35:46.080 --> 35:48.651
- You really think I should?
- Yes.

35:59.840 --> 36:01.968
Come on, Mom.

36:04.040 --> 36:08.443
- Mama, welcome to the '60s.
- Heh.

36:10.520 --> 36:13.888
- I'll talk to you after biology.
- See you after PE, guys.

36:14.040 --> 36:20.844
In the figure shown, line
segment AB and line segment CD...

36:21.000 --> 36:22.843
are chords of the circle.

36:23.000 --> 36:26.846
Line segment PA
and line segment PC...

36:27.800 --> 36:30.849
What is the problem, Mr. Davis?

36:31.040 --> 36:33.520
I can't see through her hair.

36:33.680 --> 36:35.250
I can't help it if he's short.

36:35.400 --> 36:40.884
Your ratted hair is preventing yet
another student's geometry education.

36:41.320 --> 36:43.641
It's feathered, not ratted.

36:43.840 --> 36:47.640
Whatever you call it,
it's a hair-don't.

36:47.840 --> 36:49.968
You've been warned repeatedly.

36:50.200 --> 36:54.171
I want you to take a little walk
down to the principal's office.

36:54.320 --> 36:56.049
Let's see what he has to say.

37:13.440 --> 37:16.250
Anyway, she was right in the car...

37:16.400 --> 37:20.724
in plain sight of
just everybody at the hop.

37:20.920 --> 37:22.251
She was nude.

37:22.400 --> 37:24.289
- No.
- That fat thing?

37:24.440 --> 37:27.011
Tracy Turnblad is a whore.

37:30.280 --> 37:31.327
Happy now?

37:31.480 --> 37:33.687
- But, Mom, I didn't do...
- Don't "but, Mom" me.

37:33.840 --> 37:36.810
- I didn't. He's lying. Ow!
- You are suspended.

37:36.960 --> 37:40.203
- What was that for?
- Give you something to whine about.

37:47.800 --> 37:50.485
Miss Turnblad?

37:56.760 --> 37:58.125
Have a seat.

37:58.280 --> 38:00.282
Yes, sir.

38:04.880 --> 38:08.566
Once again, your hairdo
is getting you in hot water.

38:08.760 --> 38:12.401
Didn't two weeks in hairdo
detention have any effect?

38:13.120 --> 38:15.726
Uh, I happen to be the
height of teen fashion.

38:15.880 --> 38:19.407
You're on a one-way ticket
to reform school.

38:19.600 --> 38:22.843
Well, I'm afraid we're just going
to have to change your homeroom.

38:23.000 --> 38:28.131
Starting today, you report
to class 10-D, room 108.

38:28.320 --> 38:29.481
Special ed?

38:29.680 --> 38:33.082
Yes, Miss Turnblad,
special education.

38:33.280 --> 38:35.248
- But that's for retards.
- Mm.

38:35.400 --> 38:37.243
And the black kids
you try to hold back.

38:37.400 --> 38:39.971
Here, you will be taught
by specialists...

38:40.120 --> 38:44.125
trained to deal with hairdo
scofflaws in high-school society.

38:44.280 --> 38:45.930
Mr. Davidson.

38:46.120 --> 38:48.168
That will be all, Miss Turnblad.

38:48.360 --> 38:52.285
The city of Baltimore
has an interesting Catholic history.

38:52.440 --> 38:54.283
It was named after Lord Baltimore.

38:54.440 --> 38:56.841
He founded the Maryland
colony for Catholics...

38:57.000 --> 39:00.846
and others who could not practice
their religion in England.

39:08.960 --> 39:12.806
Hey, don't touch my stuff.
I'll kick your ass.

39:12.960 --> 39:14.769
Take it back.

39:28.920 --> 39:31.446
Teach us how to dance, honey.

39:41.480 --> 39:45.883
Yeah, yeah. Go, go, go...

39:48.840 --> 39:50.842
Good morning, class.

39:51.040 --> 39:53.361
Good morning, Mrs. Shipley.

39:53.800 --> 39:57.805
Now let's all stand and say
the Pledge of Allegiance.

40:06.360 --> 40:09.443
I pledge allegiance to the flag...

40:09.600 --> 40:11.648
of the United States of America.

40:16.000 --> 40:19.004
And one and two and three and four.

40:19.160 --> 40:21.606
Let's warm it up.
And one and two...

40:21.760 --> 40:24.525
Come on, Amber.
Can't we just be friends?

40:25.880 --> 40:27.245
You're acting like a child.

40:27.440 --> 40:29.522
Here we go with jumping jacks.

40:29.680 --> 40:33.480
Let's go.
And one and two and three...

40:33.640 --> 40:34.846
Now, as you all know...

40:35.000 --> 40:37.924
today is special education's turn
at the dodgeball tournament.

40:38.120 --> 40:39.451
Aw!

40:42.160 --> 40:45.164
So let's get into the locker room,
put on those gym outfits...

40:45.320 --> 40:49.291
and show them that special education
is nothing to laugh about.

40:49.920 --> 40:52.161
And three and four.
Looking good.

40:52.320 --> 40:53.810
Look, it's special ed.

41:00.760 --> 41:03.127
This is special ed?

41:14.360 --> 41:16.089
Special ed in the red!

41:17.840 --> 41:21.367
All right, ladies, let's go.
Let's play dodgeball.

41:23.400 --> 41:26.006
Penny, they put me in special ed
just because of my hair.

41:28.240 --> 41:30.561
Hey, I saw you on
<i>The Corny Collins Show.</i>

41:30.720 --> 41:32.927
Where'd a white girl learn
to dance like that?

41:33.080 --> 41:34.127
Just practicing.

41:34.280 --> 41:36.851
Oh, and watching Negro Day
on Corny Collins.

41:37.040 --> 41:39.407
Hey, Thunder Thighs,
this one's for you.

