01:17:46.840 --> 01:17:49.411
The moment of truth
has arrived, ladies and gentlemen.

01:17:49.600 --> 01:17:52.046
- You, the audience, made your decision.
- Excuse me.

01:17:52.200 --> 01:17:55.807
And here to announce the
results we have Mr. Arvin Hodgepile...

01:17:55.960 --> 01:17:58.531
president of WZZT studios,
ladies and gentlemen.

01:18:00.120 --> 01:18:03.249
Thank you. Thank you.

01:18:03.440 --> 01:18:06.489
We have a difficult situation
with the votes tabulation.

01:18:06.640 --> 01:18:08.881
The results were quite close.

01:18:09.040 --> 01:18:12.487
<i>Tracy! Tracy! Tracy!</i>

01:18:12.680 --> 01:18:18.528
<i>Tracy! Tracy! Tracy!</i>

01:18:18.680 --> 01:18:22.366
Technically, the winner is
Miss Tracy Turnblad.

01:18:22.520 --> 01:18:23.965
<i>Yeah!</i>

01:18:37.040 --> 01:18:39.805
Wait a minute.
Wait a minute. Quiet.

01:18:40.000 --> 01:18:43.482
Shut up, or we're
going off the air.

01:18:43.640 --> 01:18:45.290
Now listen carefully.

01:18:45.440 --> 01:18:49.729
Since Miss Turnblad is in reform school,
the judges have found her ineligible.

01:18:51.640 --> 01:18:54.450
I would like to announce
on behalf of WZZT...

01:18:54.600 --> 01:18:59.811
the winner of the Miss Auto Show
1963, Amber Von Tussle.

01:19:39.800 --> 01:19:42.644
Let's talk this over.
We can discuss this.

01:19:42.800 --> 01:19:45.724
Oh, what...? Oh, wow.
Let's talk it over.

01:19:45.920 --> 01:19:48.287
- Leave him alone.
- We can talk... I'll call.

01:19:50.760 --> 01:19:55.049
Well, Amber, like it or not,
you're officially Miss Auto Show 1963.

01:19:56.840 --> 01:20:00.845
Any words for your opponent who
many feel was the more popular winner?

01:20:01.000 --> 01:20:04.686
I'd like to lead a dance
and dedicate it to that loser.

01:20:04.840 --> 01:20:09.607
Tracy Turnblad, I hope you're watching,
because this one's for you.

01:20:09.760 --> 01:20:14.004
It's a brand-new dance, one that
I'm sure you'll know how to do.

01:20:14.200 --> 01:20:15.531
It's called the Roach.

01:20:16.120 --> 01:20:18.043
<i>Too bad you can't be
here to do it.</i>

01:20:18.200 --> 01:20:21.522
I'm the winner!
Leave me alone!

01:20:21.680 --> 01:20:23.808
Amber Von Tussle and the Roach.

01:20:32.280 --> 01:20:35.727
<i>There's a dance
They're callin' the Roach</i>

01:20:35.880 --> 01:20:39.282
<i>It's buggin' all the kids
From coast to coast</i>

01:20:39.440 --> 01:20:45.641
<i>Well now, form a big line
Do the Roach</i>

01:20:45.800 --> 01:20:50.601
<i>Everybody, now
Squish, squash</i>

01:20:50.760 --> 01:20:52.649
<i>Kill that roach</i>

01:20:54.240 --> 01:20:57.642
<i>Well, there's a roach
Upon my floor</i>

01:20:57.800 --> 01:21:00.007
For Christ's sakes,
pardon Tracy Turnblad.

01:21:00.160 --> 01:21:01.730
- All right!
- Whoo!

01:21:02.080 --> 01:21:04.686
<i>Free Tracy Turnblad!</i>

01:21:56.000 --> 01:22:01.450
<i>Squish, squash
Kill that roach</i>

01:22:18.640 --> 01:22:20.244
Tracy?
What are you doing here?

01:22:32.440 --> 01:22:33.521
I got something for you.

01:22:36.560 --> 01:22:38.130
Amber.

01:22:38.880 --> 01:22:41.804
Wait. Hold on.

01:22:42.720 --> 01:22:46.327
Baltimore, you are seeing
history being made today.

01:22:46.520 --> 01:22:51.162
White and black together
for the first time on local TV.

01:22:51.400 --> 01:22:54.927
- I hate you, Tracy Turnblad.
- <i>The Corny Collins Show</i> is integrated!

01:22:55.080 --> 01:22:56.366
Yes, all right!

01:23:10.480 --> 01:23:13.404
Amber, we're going home now.

01:23:13.560 --> 01:23:15.324
No, Mommy, no!

01:23:36.400 --> 01:23:38.801
Stop. Get away from me.
Get away. Come on.

01:23:38.960 --> 01:23:41.611
I'm a married man with a family.
Don't hurt me, please.

01:23:47.000 --> 01:23:49.082
Thank you. Thank you.

01:23:49.240 --> 01:23:51.368
I love you, Baltimore.

01:23:57.320 --> 01:24:01.086
I don't know about you,
but I feel like dancing.

01:24:02.960 --> 01:24:05.850
I've got the Bug.

01:24:15.240 --> 01:24:18.164
<i>Everybody's jumpin'
Movin' around</i>

01:24:18.360 --> 01:24:20.840
<i>Nobody's standin' still
Keepin' their ground</i>

01:24:21.000 --> 01:24:24.209
<i>You can't tell what'll happen
When they pass it around</i>

01:24:24.360 --> 01:24:26.169
<i>It's the bug</i>

01:24:27.880 --> 01:24:30.645
<i>You got it, you got it
You're all on your own</i>

01:24:30.800 --> 01:24:34.327
<i>Somehow it seems better
When you do it alone</i>

01:24:34.880 --> 01:24:36.723
- What are you doing? Ow!
- Give me that.

01:24:36.920 --> 01:24:38.809
You little... Ugh.

01:24:40.360 --> 01:24:43.648
<i>Well, come on, baby
Let's do the Bug</i>

01:24:43.800 --> 01:24:47.361
<i>Mm, come on, baby
And give me a hug</i>

01:24:47.560 --> 01:24:50.086
<i>Come on, baby
My turn's long due</i>

01:24:50.240 --> 01:24:53.210
<i>I wanna Bug
Bug a hole in my shoe</i>

01:24:53.360 --> 01:24:56.523
<i>Well, real bugs bug me
No matter what size</i>

01:24:56.680 --> 01:24:58.125
Come down. Come down.

01:24:58.320 --> 01:25:00.368
- Itching powder.
- Itching powder?

01:25:00.520 --> 01:25:02.522
Oh, oh, oh!

01:26:15.680 --> 01:26:18.923
- Let's dance!
- Yeah!

